						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1308, Kshaya, Vaiśākha, śu. 1, Va[ḍḍavāra],</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1386 March 31 Saturday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Hariyappa-Oḍeya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Chikkatamma,</hi> son of Kalli-Gauḍa of <hi rend="bold">Eṟaganahaḷḷi,</hi> died after slaying thieves with an axe in <hi rend="bold">Mūḍaṇabeṭṭa</hi> and that his younger brother Kētaṇṇa set up this hero-stone.</p>						

						<p>First Section.</p>						

